juniMplsMIB.name: juniMplsMIB

revisions.description: Changed the upper bound value of juniMplsGroupLdpSessionRetries from 128 to 65535.
Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names. Added IP TTL Propagate object to the MPLS scalar group.

Fixed SMIv2 conformance. Added RowStatus support to juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionTable, juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionTable, juniMplsTunnelProfileDynamicEndpointTable and juniMplsTunnelProfileTunnelEndpointTable.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniMplsMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniMplsMIB.description: The MultiProtocol Label Switching (MPLS) MIB for the Juniper Networks enterprise. This MIB contains managed objects for basic MPLS configuration of: 1. Global tasks - common MPLS usage configurations on a given label switching router (LSR). 2. Interface tasks - MPLS interface (major interface) configurations. 3. Tunnel tasks - tunnel interface (minor interface) configurations. 4. Tunnel profile tasks - configured to be used by multiple MPLS tunnels. 5. Explicit paths - supports dynamic and manual configurations of explicit paths. 6. VPNs - supports constraint-based routing label distribution protocol (CR-LDP) and BGP/MPLS virtual private network (VPN) configurations.

JuniMajorCfgVciRanges.name: JuniMajorCfgVciRanges
JuniMajorCfgVciRanges.description: Generic VCI label range specifier for both resource reservation protocol (RSVP) and label distribution protocol (LDP).

JuniMajorCfgVpiRanges.name: JuniMajorCfgVpiRanges
JuniMajorCfgVpiRanges.description: Generic VPI label range specifier for both resource reservation protocol (RSVP) and label distribution protocol (LDP).

JuniMinorCfgBWRanges.name: JuniMinorCfgBWRanges
JuniMinorCfgBWRanges.description: Specifies bandwidth requirements for each MPLS tunnel.

JuniMinorCfgHoldingAndSetupPriorityRange.name: JuniMinorCfgHoldingAndSetupPriorityRanges
JuniMinorCfgHoldingAndSetupPriorityRange.description: Each LSP has a setup and hold priority before setting it up or preempting it relative to the other LSPs. This convention specifies those ranges.

JuniMinorCfgRetryTimesAndNorouteRanges.name: JuniMinorCfgRetryTimesAndNorouteRanges
JuniMinorCfgRetryTimesAndNorouteRanges.description: RSVP/LDP will have a number of retries for successfully setting up a tunnel. This value specifies retry value ranges for LDP/RSVP with or without no-route notification.

JuniMinorCfgRetryIntervalAndNorouteRange.name: JuniMinorCfgRetryIntervalAndNorouteRanges
JuniMinorCfgRetryIntervalAndNorouteRange.description: RSVP/LDP will have time interval between two successive retries for setting up tunnel successfully. This value specifies the interval ranges for LDP/RSVP with or without no-route notification.

JuniProfileCfgBWRanges.name: JuniProfileCfgBWRanges
JuniProfileCfgBWRanges.description: Bandwidth range specified for each tunnel in tunnel profiling.

JuniProfileCfgHoldingAndSetupPriorityRan.name: JuniProfileCfgHoldingAndSetupPriorityRanges
JuniProfileCfgHoldingAndSetupPriorityRan.description: Tunnel setup and hold priority range specified for each tunnel in tunnel profile configuration.

JuniProfileCfgRetryTimesAndNorouteRanges.name: JuniProfileCfgRetryTimesAndNorouteRanges
JuniProfileCfgRetryTimesAndNorouteRanges.description: Range specified for number of retries for tunnel with or without no-route notification for RSVP/LDP.

JuniProfileCfgRetryIntervalAndNorouteRan.name: JuniProfileCfgRetryIntervalAndNorouteRanges
JuniProfileCfgRetryIntervalAndNorouteRan.description: Range specified for retry interval for tunnel with or without no-route notification for RSVP/LDP.

juniMplsGroupMplsEnable.name: juniMplsGroupMplsEnable
juniMplsGroupMplsEnable.description: Enables or disables MPLS on the virtual router. When MPLS is created on the virtual router (VR), it remains adminstratively disabled untill it is enabled explicitly. Without administratively enabling the MPLS on VR, it won't function as an LSR even though it holds the MPLS configurations until the MPLS context is destroyed for the VR.

juniMplsGroupReopTimer.name: juniMplsGroupReopTimer
juniMplsGroupReopTimer.description: All LSPs setup in MPLS domain are reoptimized for better LSPs as and when available. This object allows configuration of the frequency of reoptimization in time interval.

juniMplsGroupLabelRangeLow.name: juniMplsGroupLabelRangeLow
juniMplsGroupLabelRangeLow.description: The lower end of the range of the platform label space from which the interfaces on a given LSR derive their label space. Ethernet interfaces can use only platform label space while ATM interfaces can use either platform or interface label space. For the successful configuration of the label range both lower and higher end values must be set cuncurrently.

juniMplsGroupLabelRangeHigh.name: juniMplsGroupLabelRangeHigh
juniMplsGroupLabelRangeHigh.description: The higher end of the range of the platform label space from which the interfaces on a given LSR derive their label space. Ethernet interfaces can use only platform label space while ATM interfaces can use either platform or interface label space. For the successful configuration of the label range both lower and higher end values must be set cuncurrently.

juniMplsGroupLspRetryTimesNoroute.name: juniMplsGroupLspRetryTimesNoroute
juniMplsGroupLspRetryTimesNoroute.description: This object configures the number of retries for LSP setup after a failure due to no available route.

juniMplsGroupLspRetryIntervalNoroute.name: juniMplsGroupLspRetryIntervalNoroute
juniMplsGroupLspRetryIntervalNoroute.description: This object configures the time interval between two successive LSP setup retries after a failure due to no available route.

juniMplsGroupLspRetryTimes.name: juniMplsGroupLspRetryTimes
juniMplsGroupLspRetryTimes.description: Use this object to configure number of retries for LSP setup after a failure other than one due to no available route.

juniMplsGroupLspRetryInterval.name: juniMplsGroupLspRetryInterval
juniMplsGroupLspRetryInterval.description: Use this object to configure the time interval between two LSP setup retries after a failure other than one due to no available route.

juniMplsGroupLdpRetryTimesNoroute.name: juniMplsGroupLdpRetryTimesNoroute
juniMplsGroupLdpRetryTimesNoroute.description: Use this object to configure the number of retries for LDP to setup LSP after a failure due to no available route.

juniMplsGroupLdpRetryIntervalNoroute.name: juniMplsGroupLdpRetryIntervalNoroute
juniMplsGroupLdpRetryIntervalNoroute.description: Use this object to configure the time interval between two successive LSP setup retries by LDP after a failure due to no available route.

juniMplsGroupLdpRetryTimes.name: juniMplsGroupLdpRetryTimes
juniMplsGroupLdpRetryTimes.description: Use this object to configure LSP setup retries by LDP after a failure other than one due to no available route.

juniMplsGroupLdpRetryInterval.name: juniMplsGroupLdpRetryInterval
juniMplsGroupLdpRetryInterval.description: Use this object to configure time interval between two LSP setup retries by LDP after a failure other than one due to no available route.

juniMplsGroupLdpSessionRetries.name: juniMplsGroupLdpSessionRetries
juniMplsGroupLdpSessionRetries.description: Use this object to configure the number of LDP session retries.

juniMplsGroupLdpSessionRetryTimer.name: juniMplsGroupLdpSessionRetryTimer
juniMplsGroupLdpSessionRetryTimer.description: Use this object to configure the time interval between two LDP session retries.

juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenIpProfileName.name: juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenIpProfileName
juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenIpProfileName.description: Usually IP interfaces are stacked on top of the MPLS tunnels. The profiled tunnels are associated with IP interfaces with profile of IP interfaces. This object configures the name for the IP profile.

juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIn.name: juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIntf
juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIn.description: This object allows enabling/disabling of IP interfaces created over egress LSPs setup by topology driven LSP setup configurations.

juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpI.name: juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIntf
juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpI.description: This object allows enabling/disabling of IP interfaces created over ingress LSPs setup by topology driven LSP setup configurations.

juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIn.name: juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIntfHostOnly
juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIn.description: This object allows enabling/disabling of IP interfaces created over egress LSPs to host only IP addresses setup by topology driven LSP setup configurations.

juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpI.name: juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIntfHostOnly
juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpI.description: This object allows enabling/disabling of IP interfaces created over ingress LSPs to host only IP addresses setup by topology driven LSP setup configurations.

juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIn.name: juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIntfPolicyListType
juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIn.description: There are two types of policy list type defined for the locally defined labels advertisement to neighbors; viz. accessList and prefixList. This object allows configuration of the egress side of LSR for topology driven LSPs. Set the list type and list name cuncurrently.

juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpI.name: juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIntfPolicyListType
juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpI.description: There are two types of policy list type defined for the locally defined labels advertisement to neighbors; viz. accessList and prefixList. This object allows configuration of the ingress side of LSR for topology driven LSPs. Set the list type and list name cuncurrently.

juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIn.name: juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIntfPolicyList
juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIn.description: This object used to configure egress list name of topology driven LSPs over IP interfaces. For successful configurations the egress list name must be set cunncurently with egress list type. Set the list type and list name cuncurrently.

juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpI.name: juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIntfPolicyList
juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpI.description: This object used to configure ingress list name of topology driven LSPs over IP interfaces. For successful configurations ingress listname set cunncurently with ingress list type. Set the list type and list name cuncurrently.

juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdp.name: juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdp
juniMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdp.description: LDP is used for label distributions control for setting up the LSPs. Topology driven LSPs also setup using LDP label distribution control. This object allows to enable/disable LDP admin state used for topology driven LSPs setup.

juniMplsGroupLspLabelDistCtrlMode.name: juniMplsGroupLspLabelDistCtrlMode
juniMplsGroupLspLabelDistCtrlMode.description: Some FECs correspond to address prefixes which are distributed via a dynamic routing algorithm. The setup of the LSPs for these FECs can be done in one of two ways: Independent LSP Control or Ordered LSP Control. This object displays the LSP lable distribution control mode.

juniMplsGroupLdpAdvHostOnly.name: juniMplsGroupLdpAdvHostOnly
juniMplsGroupLdpAdvHostOnly.description: This object allows to enable/disable LDP label advertisement mode for host only LSPs.

juniMplsGroupLsrState.name: juniMplsGroupLsrState
juniMplsGroupLsrState.description: This object value displays the status of MPLS enabled LSR such as state is up or down etc.

juniMplsGroupReopNow.name: juniMplsGroupReopNow
juniMplsGroupReopNow.description: All LSPs setup in MPLS domain are reoptimized for better LSPs as and when available. Setting this object forces an immediate check for better paths for the existing LSPs.

juniMplsGroupIpTtlPropagate.name: juniMplsGroupIpTtlPropagate
juniMplsGroupIpTtlPropagate.description: Indicate the IP TTL propagation status on ingress LSPs. none - Not set to anything. hideForwardedAndLocal - Hide LSP topology from local and forwarded traffic. hideForwarded - Hide LSP topology from forwarded traffic only. hideLocal - Hide LSP topology from local traffic only.

juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendTable.name: juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendTable
juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendTable.description: This table contains list of send side IP addresses for LDP targeted hello messages.

juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendEntry.name: juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendEntry
juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendEntry.description: Each entry represents send IP address for targeted hello message.

juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendAddress.name: juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendAddress
juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendAddress.description: Configure the send side address for targeted hello messages.

juniMplsGroupLdpTargetedHelloSendMode.name: juniMplsGroupLdpTargetedHelloSendMode
juniMplsGroupLdpTargetedHelloSendMode.description: Select mode to add/delete to the list of IP addresses for targeted hello messages.

juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveTable.name: juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveTable
juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveTable.description: This table contains list of receive side IP addresses for LDP targeted hello messages.

juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveEntry.name: juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveEntry
juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveEntry.description: Each entry represents receive IP address for targeted hello message.

juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveAddress.name: juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveAddress
juniMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveAddress.description: Configure the receive side address for targeted hello messages.

juniMplsGroupLdpTargetedHelloReceiveMode.name: juniMplsGroupLdpTargetedHelloReceiveMode
juniMplsGroupLdpTargetedHelloReceiveMode.description: Select mode to add/delete to the list of IP addresses for targeted hello messages.

juniMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListTable.name: juniMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListTable
juniMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListTable.description: Table is a list of LDP label advertisement entries.

juniMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListEntry.name: juniMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListEntry
juniMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListEntry.description: Each entry represents access list pairs for the LDP peers label advertisement.

juniMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListName.name: juniMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListName
juniMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListName.description: This LDP label advertisement route list name for which this entry contains information.

juniMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverNbrListName.name: juniMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverNbrListName
juniMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverNbrListName.description: The LDP label advertisement neighbor route list name for which this entry contains information.

juniMplsGroupLabelAdverListMode.name: juniMplsGroupLabelAdverListMode
juniMplsGroupLabelAdverListMode.description: This object selects the mode of addition/deletion to the list.

juniMplsGroupLdpProfileTable.name: juniMplsGroupLdpProfileTable
juniMplsGroupLdpProfileTable.description: Table is a list of LDP Profile entries.

juniMplsGroupLdpProfileEntry.name: juniMplsGroupLdpProfileEntry
juniMplsGroupLdpProfileEntry.description: Each entry represents one LDP profile settings.

juniMplsGroupLdpProfileName.name: juniMplsGroupLdpProfileName
juniMplsGroupLdpProfileName.description: LDP profile name identifies unique entry in the table.

juniMplsGroupLdpProfileHelloHoldTime.name: juniMplsGroupLdpProfileHelloHoldTime
juniMplsGroupLdpProfileHelloHoldTime.description: Configure the LDP peers hello hold time period.

juniMplsGroupLdpProfileCrLdpAdminState.name: juniMplsGroupLdpProfileCrLdpAdminState
juniMplsGroupLdpProfileCrLdpAdminState.description: Enable or disable the constraint-based routing label distribution protocol (CR-LDP) admin state.

juniMplsGroupLdpProfileRowStatus.name: juniMplsGroupLdpProfileRowStatus
juniMplsGroupLdpProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniMplsGroupLdpProfileCrLdpAdminState juniMplsGroupLdpProfileRowStatus

juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileTable.name: juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileTable
juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileTable.description: Table is a list of LDP Profile entries.

juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileEntry.name: juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileEntry
juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileEntry.description: Each entry represents one LDP profile settings.

juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileName.name: juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileName
juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileName.description: The RSVP profile name identifies unique entry in the table.

juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileRefreshPeriod.name: juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileRefreshPeriod
juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileRefreshPeriod.description: Configure the time out period between the generation of two refresh messages.

juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileCleanupTimeoutFa.name: juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileCleanupTimeoutFactor
juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileCleanupTimeoutFa.description: Confgure the number of refresh messages can be lost before PATH or RESV state is ended.

juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileRowStatus.name: juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileRowStatus
juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry object MUST be explicitly configured: juniMplsGroupRsvpProfileRowStatus

juniMplsIfMajorNextIfIndex.name: juniMplsIfMajorNextIfIndex
juniMplsIfMajorNextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in the juniMplsIfMajorTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

juniMplsIfMajorTable.name: juniMplsIfMajorTable
juniMplsIfMajorTable.description: This table contains entries for MPLS Major interfaces present in the system.

juniMplsIfMajorEntry.name: juniMplsIfMajorEntry
juniMplsIfMajorEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an MPLS Major interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries to be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable.

juniMplsIfMajorIndex.name: juniMplsIfMajorIndex
juniMplsIfMajorIndex.description: The ifIndex of the MPLS Major interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading juniMplsIfMajorNextIfIndex.

juniMplsIfMajorRowStatus.name: juniMplsIfMajorRowStatus
juniMplsIfMajorRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniMplsIfMajorRowStatus juniMplsIfMajorLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for juniMplsIfMajorIndex must have been determined previously, by reading juniMplsIfMajorNextIfIndex. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable is created/ destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

juniMplsIfMajorLowerIfIndex.name: juniMplsIfMajorLowerIfIndex
juniMplsIfMajorLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an interface over which this MPLS Major interface to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

juniMplsIfMajorAdminStatus.name: juniMplsIfMajorAdminStatus
juniMplsIfMajorAdminStatus.description: Use this object to create MPLS major interface stacked over any link layer interface. Lower layer(index) over which major stacks has to be specified for successful creation of the major interface.

juniMplsIfMajorLdpAdminStatus.name: juniMplsIfMajorLdpAdminStatus
juniMplsIfMajorLdpAdminStatus.description: This object enables/disables LDP admin status on the MPLS interface.

juniMplsIfMajorLdpProfileName.name: juniMplsIfMajorLdpProfileName
juniMplsIfMajorLdpProfileName.description: All the LDP settings on the MPLS interface be will associated with the profile. This object allows to associate those configured settings to interface by using the LDP profile name.

juniMplsIfMajorLdpVpiStart.name: juniMplsIfMajorLdpVpiStart
juniMplsIfMajorLdpVpiStart.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the start range of the LDP VPI. For successful configuration of interface label space LDP VPI ranges, set this object with the stop range cunncurrently.

juniMplsIfMajorLdpVpiStop.name: juniMplsIfMajorLdpVpiStop
juniMplsIfMajorLdpVpiStop.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the stop range of the LDP VPI. For successful configuration of interface label space LDP VPI ranges, set this object with the start range cunncurrently.

juniMplsIfMajorLdpVciStart.name: juniMplsIfMajorLdpVciStart
juniMplsIfMajorLdpVciStart.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the start range of the LDP VCI. For successful configuration of interface label space LDP VCI ranges, set this object with the stop range cunncurrently.

juniMplsIfMajorLdpVciStop.name: juniMplsIfMajorLdpVciStop
juniMplsIfMajorLdpVciStop.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the stop range of the LDP VCI. For successful configuration of interface label space LDP VCI ranges, set this object with the start range cunncurrently.

juniMplsIfMajorRsvpAdminStatus.name: juniMplsIfMajorRsvpAdminStatus
juniMplsIfMajorRsvpAdminStatus.description: This object configures RSVP admin status for MPLS interface.

juniMplsIfMajorRsvpProfileName.name: juniMplsIfMajorRsvpProfileName
juniMplsIfMajorRsvpProfileName.description: All the RSVP settings on the MPLS interface be will associated with the profile. This object allows to associate those configured settings to interface by using the RSVP profile name.

juniMplsIfMajorRsvpVpiStart.name: juniMplsIfMajorRsvpVpiStart
juniMplsIfMajorRsvpVpiStart.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the start range of the RSVP VPI. For successful configuration of interface label space RSVP VPI ranges, set this object with the stop range cunncurrently.

juniMplsIfMajorRsvpVpiStop.name: juniMplsIfMajorRsvpVpiStop
juniMplsIfMajorRsvpVpiStop.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the stop range of the RSVP VPI. For successful configuration of interface label space RSVP VPI ranges, set this object with the start range cunncurrently.

juniMplsIfMajorRsvpVciStart.name: juniMplsIfMajorRsvpVciStart
juniMplsIfMajorRsvpVciStart.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the start range of the RSVP VCI. For successful configuration of interface label space RSVP VCI ranges, set this object with the stop range cunncurrently.

juniMplsIfMajorRsvpVciStop.name: juniMplsIfMajorRsvpVciStop
juniMplsIfMajorRsvpVciStop.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the stop range of the RSVP VCI. For successful configuration of interface label space RSVP VCI ranges, set this object with the start range cunncurrently.

juniMplsIfMajorLabelSpaceType.name: juniMplsIfMajorLabelSpaceType
juniMplsIfMajorLabelSpaceType.description: Displays the label space type for the MPLS interface.

juniMplsIfMajorOpState.name: juniMplsIfMajorOpState
juniMplsIfMajorOpState.description: This object displays MPLS major interface operation state.

juniMplsIfMajorCrLdpAdminState.name: juniMplsIfMajorCrLdpAdminState
juniMplsIfMajorCrLdpAdminState.description: This object displays the admin state of CR-LDP.

juniMplsIfMinorNextIfIndex.name: juniMplsIfMinorNextIfIndex
juniMplsIfMinorNextIfIndex.description: Coordinates ifIndex value allocation for entries in the juniMplsIfMinorTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

juniMplsIfMinorTable.name: juniMplsIfMinorTable
juniMplsIfMinorTable.description: This table contains entries for MPLS Minor interfaces present in the system.

juniMplsIfMinorEntry.name: juniMplsIfMinorEntry
juniMplsIfMinorEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an MPLS Minor interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable.

juniMplsIfMinorIndex.name: juniMplsIfMinorIndex
juniMplsIfMinorIndex.description: The ifIndex of the MPLS Minor interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading juniMplsMinorNextIfIndex.

juniMplsIfMinorRowStatus.name: juniMplsIfMinorRowStatus
juniMplsIfMinorRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create/delete an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniMplsIfMinorRowStatus juniMplsIfMinorTunnelName In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for juniMplsIfMinorIndex must have been determined previously, by reading juniMplsMinorNextIfIndex. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable is created/ destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

juniMplsIfMinorLowerIfIndex.name: juniMplsIfMinorLowerIfIndex
juniMplsIfMinorLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an interface over which this MPLS Minor interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. As minor interface can be created without stacking on major interface, as and when it stacks on major interface by signalling protocol, it's value can be read.

juniMplsIfMinorAdminStatus.name: juniMplsIfMinorAdminStatus
juniMplsIfMinorAdminStatus.description: With this object minor interface admin status can be enabled/disabled.

juniMplsIfMinorEndpointAddress.name: juniMplsIfMinorEndpointAddress
juniMplsIfMinorEndpointAddress.description: This object configures the IP address of the tunnel destination. This object can be set along with the juniMplsIfMinorEndpointDstMask to configure the tunnel destination mask, but it is optional.

juniMplsIfMinorEndpointDstMask.name: juniMplsIfMinorEndpointDstMask
juniMplsIfMinorEndpointDstMask.description: This object configures the tunnel destination mask. It can be set along with the juniMplsIfMinorEndpointAddress.

juniMplsIfMinorTunnelMetricMode.name: juniMplsIfMinorTunnelMetricMode
juniMplsIfMinorTunnelMetricMode.description: Select the relative or absolute mode to configure the absolute or relative tunnel metric. To set the tunnel to relative metric, juniMplsIfMinorRelativeTunnelMetric has to be set along with this object option as relative. To set the tunnel to absolute metric, juniMplsIfMinorAbsoluteTunnelMetric has to be set along with this object option as absolute.

juniMplsIfMinorAbsoluteTunnelMetric.name: juniMplsIfMinorAbsoluteTunnelMetric
juniMplsIfMinorAbsoluteTunnelMetric.description: This object allows configuration of absolute metric values. Refer to juniMplsIfMinorTunnelMetricMode for how set it.

juniMplsIfMinorAnnounceToOspf.description: This object allows to register LSP endpoints to OSPF to next hop calculation.

juniMplsIfMinorAnnounceToIsis.name: juniMplsIfMinorAnnounceToIsis
juniMplsIfMinorAnnounceToIsis.description: This object allows to register LSP endpoints to IS-IS for next hop calculation.

juniMplsIfMinorAnnounceToBgp.name: juniMplsIfMinorAnnounceToBgp
juniMplsIfMinorAnnounceToBgp.description: This object allows to register LSP endpoints to BGP for next hop calculation.

juniMplsIfMinorBandwidth.name: juniMplsIfMinorBandwidth
juniMplsIfMinorBandwidth.description: This object allows configuration of bandwidth requirements for the tunnel.

juniMplsIfMinorAffinity.description: This object allows configuration of resource class affinity for the tunnel.

juniMplsIfMinorAffinityMask.name: juniMplsIfMinorAffinityMask
juniMplsIfMinorAffinityMask.description: This allows to set the resource class affinity mask. Since it is a mask, set along with the affinity for successful configurations.

juniMplsIfMinorSetupPriority.name: juniMplsIfMinorSetupPriority
juniMplsIfMinorSetupPriority.description: This object allows configuration of preemption setup priority for the tunnel before and after it has been established. Lower the value higher the priority.

juniMplsIfMinorHoldingPriority.name: juniMplsIfMinorHoldingPriority
juniMplsIfMinorHoldingPriority.description: This object allows configuration of the preemption holding priority for the tunnel before and after it has been established. Lower the value higher the priority.

juniMplsIfMinorTunnelName.name: juniMplsIfMinorTunnelName
juniMplsIfMinorTunnelName.description: This object allows configuration of the tunnel name to be associated with tunnel settings.

juniMplsIfMinorTunnelRetryTimes.name: juniMplsIfMinorTunnelRetryTimes
juniMplsIfMinorTunnelRetryTimes.description: This object allows configuration of the number of retries for tunnel setup.

juniMplsIfMinorTunnelRetryInterval.name: juniMplsIfMinorTunnelRetryInterval
juniMplsIfMinorTunnelRetryInterval.description: This object allows configuration of retry interval for tunnel setup.

juniMplsIfMinorTunnelRetryTimesNoroute.name: juniMplsIfMinorTunnelRetryTimesNoroute
juniMplsIfMinorTunnelRetryTimesNoroute.description: This object allows configuration of the tunnel retries when no route notifications are received.

juniMplsIfMinorTunnelRetryIntervalNorout.name: juniMplsIfMinorTunnelRetryIntervalNoroute
juniMplsIfMinorTunnelRetryIntervalNorout.description: This object allows configuration of the tunnel retry interval when no route notifications are received.

juniMplsIfMinorBaseTunnelName.name: juniMplsIfMinorBaseTunnelName
juniMplsIfMinorBaseTunnelName.description: This object allows configuration of the base tunnel name over which all the tunnels are stacked over.

juniMplsIfMinorVpnOuiNumber.name: juniMplsIfMinorVpnOuiNumber
juniMplsIfMinorVpnOuiNumber.description: This object allows configuration of the OUI part of VPN ID.

juniMplsIfMinorVpnIndex.name: juniMplsIfMinorVpnIndex
juniMplsIfMinorVpnIndex.description: This object allows configuration of the index part of VPN ID.

juniMplsIfMinorTunnelOpState.name: juniMplsIfMinorTunnelOpState
juniMplsIfMinorTunnelOpState.description: This object displays the tunnel operation state. established : Tunnel established teNegotiation : TE Negotiation up : Tunnel Up down : Tunnel Down cfgChanged : Tunnel config changed cfgIncEn : Tunnel incomplete Config Admin State Enable cfgIncDis : Tunnel incomplete Config Admin State Disable disabled : Tunnel disabled rel : noChange : Tunnel state no change

juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionTable.name: juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionTable
juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionTable.description: Table is a list of different LSP paths as option for each LSP setup.

juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionEntry.name: juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionEntry
juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionEntry.description: Each entry represents one path option for the LSP.

juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionNumber.name: juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionNumber
juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionNumber.description: Unique number to identify each path option configured.

juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionProtocol.name: juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionProtocol
juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionProtocol.description: Select the each path option explicit routing protocol.

juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionLockdown.name: juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionLockdown
juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionLockdown.description: Enable/disable each configured path option reoptimization.

juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionPathName.name: juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionPathName
juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionPathName.description: Configure the name for each path option.

juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionPathId.name: juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionPathId
juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionPathId.description: Configure the path option ID. Either the name or ID will be associated with a path at a time. If the path name and ID are set at a same time for the path, the name will have precedence over ID.

juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionRowStatus.name: juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionRowStatus
juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniMplsIfMinorPathOptionRowStatus.

juniMplsTunnelProfileTable.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileTable
juniMplsTunnelProfileTable.description: Table is a list of tunnel profiles for a given VR.

juniMplsTunnelProfileEntry.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileEntry
juniMplsTunnelProfileEntry.description: Each entry represents one tunnel profile.

juniMplsTunnelProfileName.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileName
juniMplsTunnelProfileName.description: Associate a name for the configured tunnel profile settings.

juniMplsTunnelProfileAdminStatus.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileAdminStatus
juniMplsTunnelProfileAdminStatus.description: Enable/disable the adminstatus of the tunnel profile.

juniMplsTunnelProfileBaseTunnelName.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileBaseTunnelName
juniMplsTunnelProfileBaseTunnelName.description: Configure the base tunnel name in tunnel profile settings. This base tunnel is the one over which all the other tunnels are stacked over. Configured base tunnel name in profile settings will be associated with the actual configured base tunnel name.

juniMplsTunnelProfileIpProfileName.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileIpProfileName
juniMplsTunnelProfileIpProfileName.description: Configures the name for IP profile settings for the IP interfaces over which MPLS tunnels are stacked.

juniMplsTunnelProfileLabelDistProto.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileLabelDistProto
juniMplsTunnelProfileLabelDistProto.description: Configure the label distribution protocol to associate with a tunnel profile. Label distribution protocols are used by two LSRs to negotiate label to FEC binding to set up tunnels.

juniMplsTunnelProfileAnnounceToOspf.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileAnnounceToOspf
juniMplsTunnelProfileAnnounceToOspf.description: Configure the routing protocol for next hop calculations as OSPF.

juniMplsTunnelProfileAnnounceToIsis.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileAnnounceToIsis
juniMplsTunnelProfileAnnounceToIsis.description: Configure routing protocol for next hop calculations as ISIS.

juniMplsTunnelProfileAnnounceToBgp.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileAnnounceToBgp
juniMplsTunnelProfileAnnounceToBgp.description: Configure routing protocol for next hop calculations as BGP.

juniMplsTunnelProfileMetricMode.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileMetricMode
juniMplsTunnelProfileMetricMode.description: Select the relative or absolute mode to configure the absolute or relative tunnel profile metric. To set the tunnel profile to relative metric, juniMplsTunnelProfileRelativeMetric has to be set along with this object option as relative. To set the tunnel profile to absolute metric, juniMplsTunnelProfileAbsoluteMetric has to be set along with this object option as absolute.

juniMplsTunnelProfileAbsoluteMetric.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileAbsoluteMetric
juniMplsTunnelProfileAbsoluteMetric.description: This object allows configuration of the absolute metric values. Refer to juniMplsTunnelProfileMetricMode for how set it.

juniMplsTunnelProfileRelativeMetric.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileRelativeMetric
juniMplsTunnelProfileRelativeMetric.description: This object allows configuration of the relative metric values. Refer to juniMplsTunnelProfileMetricMode for how set it.

juniMplsTunnelProfileBandwidth.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileBandwidth
juniMplsTunnelProfileBandwidth.description: This object allows configuration of bandwidth requirements for the tunnel.

juniMplsTunnelProfileAffinity.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileAffinity
juniMplsTunnelProfileAffinity.description: This object allows configuration of the resource class affinity for the tunnel. This can set independently of juniMplsTunnelProfileAffinityMask.

juniMplsTunnelProfileAffinityMask.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileAffinityMask
juniMplsTunnelProfileAffinityMask.description: This allows configuration of which bits in the affinity must match the resource class bits. Can't be set independently; always with juniMplsTunnelProfileAffinity. Specify the value in bit mask format.

juniMplsTunnelProfileSetupPriority.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileSetupPriority
juniMplsTunnelProfileSetupPriority.description: This object configuration of the preemption setup priority for the tunnel before and after it has been established. Lower the value higher the priority.

juniMplsTunnelProfileHoldingPriority.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileHoldingPriority
juniMplsTunnelProfileHoldingPriority.description: This object allows configuration of the preemption holding priority for the tunnel before and after it has been established. Lower the value higher the priority.

juniMplsTunnelProfileRetryTimes.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileRetryTimes
juniMplsTunnelProfileRetryTimes.description: This object allows configuration of the number of retries for the tunnel setup.

juniMplsTunnelProfileRetryInterval.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileRetryInterval
juniMplsTunnelProfileRetryInterval.description: This object allows configuration of retry interval for tunnel setup.

juniMplsTunnelProfileRetryTimesNoroute.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileRetryTimesNoroute
juniMplsTunnelProfileRetryTimesNoroute.description: This object allows configuration of the tunnel retries when no route notifications are received.

juniMplsTunnelProfileRetryIntervalNorout.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileRetryIntervalNoroute
juniMplsTunnelProfileRetryIntervalNorout.description: This object allows configuration of the tunnel retry interval when no route notifications are received.

juniMplsTunnelProfileVpnOuiNumber.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileVpnOuiNumber
juniMplsTunnelProfileVpnOuiNumber.description: This object allows configuration of the OUI part of VPN ID.

juniMplsTunnelProfileVpnIndex.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileVpnIndex
juniMplsTunnelProfileVpnIndex.description: This object allows configuration of the index part of VPN ID.

juniMplsTunnelProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniMplsTunnelProfileRowStatus

juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionTable.name: juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionTable
juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionTable.description: Table is a list of different LSP paths as option for each LSP setup, configured as part of tunnel profile settings

juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionEntry.name: juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionEntry
juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionEntry.description: Each entry represents one path option for the LSP setup, configured as a part of tunnel profile settings.

juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionNumber.name: juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionNumber
juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionNumber.description: Unique identifier for the path option.

juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionPathName.name: juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionPathName
juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionPathName.description: Associate a name with each explicit path.

juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionPathId.name: juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionPathId
juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionPathId.description: Each explicit path can be associated either name or ID. This object allows configuration of the ID for the explicit path.

juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionRowStatus.name: juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionRowStatus
juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionRowStatus.

juniMplsTunnelProfileDynamicEndpointPoli.description: This object allows configuration of the dynamic tunnel policy type selection.

juniMplsTunnelProfileDynamicEndpointList.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileDynamicEndpointListName
juniMplsTunnelProfileDynamicEndpointList.description: This object allows configuration of the dynamic endpoints access list name.

juniMplsTunnelProfileDynamicEndpointRowS.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileDynamicEndpointRowStatus
juniMplsTunnelProfileDynamicEndpointRowS.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry object MUST be explicitly configured: juniMplsTunnelProfileDynamicEndpointRowStatus.

juniMplsTunnelProfileTunnelEndpointTable.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileTunnelEndpointTable

juniMplsTunnelProfileTunnelEndpointRowSt.name: juniMplsTunnelProfileTunnelEndpointRowStatus
juniMplsTunnelProfileTunnelEndpointRowSt.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniMplsTunnelProfileTunnelEndpointRowStatus.

juniMplsExplicitPathTable.name: juniMplsExplicitPathTable
juniMplsExplicitPathTable.description: Table is a list of hops configurations for explicit paths.

juniMplsExplicitPathEntry.description: Each entry represents one hop configuration for the particular explicit path.

juniMplsExplicitPathName.name: juniMplsExplicitPathName
juniMplsExplicitPathName.description: Configure the name for the explicit path used as table index.

juniMplsExplicitPathRowStatus.name: juniMplsExplicitPathRowStatus
juniMplsExplicitPathRowStatus.description: Creation/deletion of the explicit path is done through setting this object.

juniMplsExplicitPathNodeTable.description: Table is a list of configured explicit paths.

juniMplsExplicitPathNodeEntry.description: Each entry represents one hop in a particular explicit path.

juniMplsExplicitPathNodeName.name: juniMplsExplicitPathNodeName
juniMplsExplicitPathNodeName.description: Configure the name for the explicit path used in the table index.

juniMplsExplicitPathNodeIndexNumber.description: Each explicit path hop will have an index associated with it. Configure each path hop index using this object.

juniMplsExplicitPathNodeLoose.name: juniMplsExplicitPathNodeLoose
juniMplsExplicitPathNodeLoose.description: Configure the explicit path hop as strict or loose. Set along with HopAddress.

juniMplsExplicitPathNodeHopAddress.description: Configure the hop IP address to setup explicit path. Explicit path next hop will be created when the mentioned hop IP address doesn't belong to any of the existing hop even without setting the rowStatus createAndGo value. The rowStatus value is used to destroy the node.

juniMplsExplicitPathNodeHopAddressMask.name: juniMplsExplicitPathNodeHopAddressMask
juniMplsExplicitPathNodeHopAddressMask.description: Configure the hop IP address mask. Set along with hop address.

juniMplsExplicitPathNodeRowStatus.description: Use this object for deletion of the node. For node creation, this value have no effect. Setting the node with IP address create the node. To delete the node set only this object.
